Class ConcurrentHashMapNullKeyOk<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      • java.util.concurrent.ConcurrentHashMap<K,V>
        • org.transitime.utils.ConcurrentHashMapNullKeyOk<K,V>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.util.concurrent.ConcurrentMap<K,V>, java.util.Map<K,V>

    public class ConcurrentHashMapNullKeyOk<K,V>
extends java.util.concurrent.ConcurrentHashMap<K,V>
    Inherits from ConcurrentHashMap but allows null key to be used. The methods that use the key are overridden so that if null key is being used it is converted to a "". Since "" is used in place of null the key must be a String.
    Author:
    SkiBu Smith
